article.headline: Norfolk St. 74, Hampton 72
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Tony Murphy had 15 points to lead four Norfolk State players in double-digits and the Spartans held off a late Hampton rally for a 74-72 win Tuesday night. The Spartans (1-3, 1-0 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) went up 20-6 in the first eight minutes, but Hampton narrowed that margin to 42-35 just before the half. The Spartans again started strong to begin the second period, leading by 11 with 10:52 to play. But the Pirates (1-6, 0-1) went on a 10-3 run -- led by Michael Freeman's two jumpers and two free-throws -- to get within four with 5:48 left. Two free-throws by Hampton's Adrian Woodard at the 1:07 mark made it a two-point game, with Norfolk State ahead 72-70. Woodard fouled Rashid Cann with 23 seconds to play, and Cann made both shots to put the Spartans up 74-70. A layup by Rashad West made it a two-point game with 11 seconds to play. Hampton's Vincent Simpson came up with a timely steal but missed the subsequent layup, and the score stood. Tynell Dunkley had a career-high 14 points for Norfolk State, Calvin Brown scored 12 and Brandon Plummer had 10. West scored 20 and Freeman had 16 for Hampton. Demario Mattox scored 15 points. Hampton shot just 41.4 percent while Norfolk State shot 53.8 percent.
